A group of tourists have escaped with minor injuries following a flash flood at the Castle of Good Hope in Cape Town. CAPE TOWN - A group of tourists have escaped with minor injuries following a flash flood at the Castle of Good Hope in Cape Town.Emergency services were called to the scene after the incident on Saturday morning.A severe cold front has brought with it much needed rain to the Western Cape this week.ER24's Werner Vermaak says, Twelve people, including four children, escaped with minor injuries and bruises after a gush of water rushed through one of the tunnels at the Cape Castle of Good Hope on Saturday morning. Shortly before 12pm, metro EMS, medical doctors and ER24 arrived on the scene where they were escorted by local tour guide to the people that were involved. (Edited by Zamangwane Shange)